Number 25, Russia has a larger surface
area than Pluto. Number 24, Oxford
University is older than the Aztec
Empire. Number 23, France was still
executing people by guillotine when Star
Wars and New Hope hit theaters. Number
22. Nintendo was originally a trading
card company. Number 21. If the sun were
the size of a white blood cell, then the
Milky Way galaxy would be the size of
the United States. Number 20. There are
more stars in space than there are
grains of sand on every beach in the
world. Number 19. For every human on
Earth, there are 1.6 million ants.
Number 18. The total weight of all those
ants, however, is about the same as all
the humans. Number 17, on Jupiter and
Saturn, it rains diamonds. Number 16,
10% of all the photos ever taken were
taken in the last 12 months. Number 15,
Shakespeare made up the name Jessica for
his play Merchant of Venice. Number 14,
your chances of being killed by a
vending machine are actually twice as
large as your chances of being bitten by
a shark. Number 13. Nowhere in the
Humpty Dumpty nursery rhyme does it say
that Humpty Dumpty is an egg. Number 12.
Armadillos almost always give birth to
quadruplets.
Number 11. Scotland's national animal is
the unicorn.
Number 10. Apparently there are more
fake flamingos in the world than real
flamingos.
Number nine. John Tyler, the 10th
president of the United States, was born
in 1790. He has a grandson that is alive
today. Number eight, a strawberry is not
a berry. Number seven, a banana is a
berry. Number six, there's enough water
in Lake Superior to cover all of North
and South America in 1 foot of liquid.
Number five, an octopus has three
hearts. Number four, there are 10 times
more bacteria in your body than actual
body cells. Number three, there is only
one country between North Korea and
Norway. Number two, New York City is
farther south than Rome, Italy. And
number one, Maine is the closest US
state to Africa.
